3. NHANES summary statistics
   Used in: population-eval/nhanesSampler-lite.js (NHANES_STATS)

   Height and weight means and standard deviations are taken from published
   CDC NHANES summary statistics for synthetic profile generation. This lab
   does not include or redistribute individual NHANES participant records.

   Source: National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey (NHANES),
   National Center for Health Statistics, Centers for Disease Control and
   Prevention. https://www.cdc.gov/nchs/nhanes/

   Verify the specific survey cycle and summary table against current CDC
   publications before citing these values in research or external docs.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. Published nutrition and statistics formulas (standard references)
   Used in: population-eval/goalCalculator-lite.js,
            population-eval/nhanesSampler-lite.js

   The following well-known, published formulas and methods are implemented
   using their standard public coefficients and are not proprietary to this
   repository:

   - Mifflin–St Jeor basal metabolic rate equation
     (Mifflin MD, St Jeor ST, et al. Am J Clin Nutr. 1990;51(2):241-247.)
   - Hamwi ideal body weight method for adjusted body weight at BMI ≥ 30
     (Hamwi GJ. Diabetes. 1964;6:29-31.)
   - Activity multipliers commonly paired with BMR-based energy estimates
   - Box–Muller transform for normal random sampling
     (Box GEP, Muller ME. Ann Math Stat. 1958;29(2):610-611.)

   These are standard clinical and statistical references; implementers should
   cite the original publications when required by their context.

